-- Stoke City Hires Hughes as Manager to Replace Pulis, BBC Reports
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2013-05-30T06:53:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-30/stoke-city-hires-hughes-as-manager-to-replace-pulis-bbc-reports.html
English Premier League soccer club
Stoke City appointed  Mark Hughes  as manager, the British
Broadcasting Corp. reported.  The 49-year-old Hughes, who was fired as Queens Park
Rangers manager six months ago, replaces Tony Pulis, who left
Stoke by mutual consent last week.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Baynes at 
 dbaynes@bloomberg.net  